==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mandamus
<hw>Man*da"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., we
command, fr. <ets>mandare</ets> to command.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>A writ issued by a superior court and directed to some inferior
tribunal, or to some corporation or person exercising authority,
commanding the performance of some specified duty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandarin</ent>⟦br⟧
